cs.CV, cs.RO, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM 

This paper proposes a new visual object tracking dataset and benchmark, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO) sub-categories. The paper also discusses performance measures and tracking architecture implementations, which suggests that it may also belong to the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Finally, the paper deals with visual model update strategies, which suggests that it may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category.
